					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11054616#post-4213422</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11054616/scp-4556#post-4213422</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 09 Apr 2019 07:23:29 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>atomicthumbs</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>303535</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is SCP-4556, where it should be.</p> <p>Photograph is mine; aerial imagery is from the USGS and modified by me. Any resemblance to any real location is both intended and correct; this electrical cabinet exists in real life where it does in fiction, and you can visit it, if you're nice and you tread lightly.</p> <p>Copper mining at the Liberty Moly project did, in fact, cease because the copper ore contained too much fluorine, poisoning the geobacteria they were using to leach the copper out and literally killing the mine. Check out that technical report in the footnote, it's fascinating!</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">spoiler</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">unspoil</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>they try to think around the fact that the object Is Certain Things, but it goes further than that, more than they know, maybe more than they <em>can</em> know. Site-4556 is a conceptual reference to SCP-4556, after all&#8230;</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
